{\par \b Syntax:}\par TRUNCATE(value, [places])\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Truncates value to system display settings. If optional places is given, truncates value to places decimal places. If places is negative, truncates to significant digits instead.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par TRUNCATE(2.3678,2) returns 2.36\par }